(17, 30, '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Faster Approvals, Better Decisions with FLUX: An Approval Management System</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: montserrat, sans-serif;\"><br></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: montserrat, sans-serif;\">The “FLUX” Workflow Approval Management&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: montserrat, sans-serif;\">System&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: montserrat, sans-serif;\">allows business users to configure the conditions for routing and approval. Through the Unity interface (versus the administrative intense Configuration interface), a business user can alter the users, the rules, the values and the conditions for document and transaction approvals. This helps put the logic into the business users hands and frees up the system administrator from these types of logic tasks.</span><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><br></span></div><br><p></p>', 'image1715497685.jpg', '2024-05-12 07:07:36', '2024-05-12 07:08:29'),
(18, 31, '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">A TMS is an integral component of a mission-critical supply chain execution (SCE) suite of applications A TMS typically sits between an ERP or Order Management System Warehouse Management System The ERP (or OMS) application passes inbound and/or outbound orders to the TMS application which then determines the optimized transportation routing. The TMS evaluates the pool of orders; consolidates them into shipments; and determines the optimal mode / lane / carrier / route / stop assignments to minimize transportation expense within the required customer service level constraints.</span><br></p>', 'image1715501953.jpg', '2024-05-12 08:19:13', '2024-05-12 08:19:13'),
(19, 32, '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.9rem; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">Opus Technology Limited offers the advanced “PARTNER” Vendor Management System, a comprehensive solution designed to optimize vendor management processes for successful organizations in corporate, commercial, and manufacturing sectors. With our robust system, companies can efficiently manage their vendors, ensuring seamless operations and improved productivity.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.9rem; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">The system establishes policies for vendor registration and introduces new vendor request forms. With the “PARTNER” Vendor Management System (VMS), it becomes effortless to onboard new vendors and monitor supplier information. The VMS serves as a centralized repository for all vendor records and files, including insurance certificates and vendor qualifications. It provides comprehensive document control and secure access within a vendor platform. Data can be easily imported with mapping for a seamless conversion process. The system’s reporting tools enable tracking of active vendors. The “PARTNER” VMS allows for a thorough review of the audit trail, complete with time, date, and user stamps. Additionally, it offers a valuable feature for evaluating vendor performance through ratings and configurable scorecards based on specific criteria.</p>', 'image1715506513.jpg', '2024-05-12 09:35:13', '2024-05-12 09:35:13'),
